<tr bgcolor=999999>
  <td> 2 </td>
  <td> Monday, September 13 </td> 
  <td> <dl>
    <li>Chapters I-V, F. Scott Fitzgerald, <i>The Great Gatsby</i>
  </dl></td>
  <td> Come to class with two </i>written</i> questions on the reading:
<ol>
<li>A big question, as big as you can think of.  Something thematic or
large. 
<li>A "little" question.  Focus on the text.  Why did Fitzgerald use a
certain word?  Or why does he bother to tell us a certain detail?
</ol>
  </td> 
</tr>

<tr bgcolor=bbbbbb>
  <td> 3 </td>
  <td> Thursday, September 16 </td>
  <td><dl>
    <li>Chapters VI-IX, F. Scott Fitzgerald, <i>The Great Gatsby</i>
  </dl></td>
  <td>Meet in small groups.  Come to class with a few discussion
  questions on Gatsby </td>
</tr>

